<title>USA: National-Standard Co Q2 loss vs profit.</title>
<headline>National-Standard Co Q2 loss vs profit.</headline>
<dateline>NILES, Mich. 1997-04-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>($000 except per share amounts)</p>
<p> For three months ended March 31:	    1997	   1996</p>
<p> Net Sales					  63,127	 66,016</p>
<p> Operating Income/(Loss)		     (9,397)	  2,792</p>
<p> Net Income/(Loss)			    (10,687)	  1,510</p>
<p> Income/(Loss) Per Share		     (2.03)*	    .28</p>
<p> Average Shares Outstanding		5,272,000    5,374,709</p>
<p> For six months ended March 31:		1997	   1996</p>
<p> Net Sales					$123,001     $126,547</p>
<p> Operating Income/(Loss)		     (7,752)	  5,019</p>
<p> Net Income/(Loss)			     (9,950)	  5,854</p>
<p> Income/(Loss) Per Share		     (1.88)*	 1.09**</p>
<p> Average Shares Outstanding		5,291,854    5,379,684</p>
<p>*  The three- and six-month periods ended March 1997 per share data of $(2.03) and $(1.88) respectively, includes $9.9 million or $(1.87) per share and $(1.86) per share related to UK restructuring charge.</p>
<p>** The six-month period ended March 1996 per share data of $1.09 includes $0.66 per share related to the sale of shares of the Allmerica Financial Corporation.</p>
